quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  6,60,"It is He who recalls you by night, and He knows what you work by day; then He raises you up therein, that a stated term may be determined; then unto Him shall you return, then He will tell you of what you have been doing"
  6,61,"He is the Omnipotent over His servants. He sends recorders over you till, when any one of you is visited by death, Our messengers take him and they neglect not"
  6,62,"Then they are restored to God their Protector, the True. Surely His is the judgment; He is the swiftest of reckoners"
  6,63,"Say: 'Who delivers you from the shadows of land and sea? You call upon Him humbly and secretly, \"Truly, if Thou deliverest from these, we shall be among the thankful"
  6,64,"Say: 'God delivers you from them and from every distress; then you assign Him associates"
  6,65,"Say: 'He is able to send forth upon you chastisement, from above you or from under your feet, or to confuse you in sects and to make you taste the violence of one another.' Behold how We turn about the signs; haply they will understand"
  6,66,"Thy people have cried it lies; yet it is the truth. Say: 'I am not a guardian over you"
  6,67,Every tiding has its time appointed; you will surely know
  6,68,"When thou seest those who plunge into Our signs, turn away from them until they plunge into some other talk; or if Satan should make thee forget, do not sit, after the reminding, with the people of the evildoers"